GRAY, Respondent, v. MUHLHAUSER, Appellant. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. January 12, 1894.) Action by Henry Winthrop Gray, as receiver, etc., against Louis Muhlhauser, impleaded, etc. From an order denying a motion to retax plaintiff’s bill of costs, defendant appeals.

Argued before VAN BRUNT, P. J., and O’BRIEN and FOLLETT, JJ.

Ira Leo Bamberger, for appellant. George Zabriskie, for respondent. PER CURIAM.

The judgment in this case having been reversed, it is •unnecessary to decide the questions here raised upon taxation of costs. Appeal dismissed, without costs.
